I'm going home.

178
00:18:43,080 --> 00:18:44,439
Back to your father?

179
00:18:47,040 --> 00:18:48,559
I'm going to God

180
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:53,999
Don't be sad.

181
00:18:54,720 --> 00:18:57,039
You have a passion
for living, Jane.

182
00:18:58,960 --> 00:19:02,079
And one day you'll
come to the region of bliss.

183
00:19:10,520 --> 00:19:11,759
Don't leave me.

184
00:19:13,560 --> 00:19:14,759
I like to have you near

185
00:19:17,400 --> 00:19:18,639
I will not leave you.

186
00:19:23,960 --> 00:19:25,999
No one shall
take me from you

187
00:19:59,120 --> 00:20:00,119
Helen!

188
00:20:03,120 --> 00:20:04,119
Helen!

189
00:20:27,120 --> 00:20:31,399
Mr. Rivers? I wondered
if you had yet heard
of any work I could do.

190
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:34,639
I found you a situation
some time ago,

191
00:20:34,720 --> 00:20:38,599
but I've delayed telling you
because the work is lowly
and I fear you'll scorn it.

192
00:20:39,160 --> 00:20:40,879
I shan't mind what I do.

193
00:20:44,160 --> 00:20:46,999
When I took over
the parish two years ago
it had no school

194
00:20:48,240 --> 00:20:51,719
I opened one for boys
I now intend to
open one for girls.

195
00:20:53,400 --> 00:20:55,679
The schoolmistress
will have a cottage paid
for by benefactors

196
00:20:55,760 --> 00:20:57,959
and she'll receive
£15 a year.

197
00:20:59,120 --> 00:21:02,279
You can see how humble,
how ignoble it is.

198
00:21:02,520 --> 00:21:04,279
Mr. Rivers,
thank you.

199
00:21:04,400 --> 00:21:05,599
I accept.

200
00:21:06,640 --> 00:21:07,839
With all my heart

201
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:09,239
But you comprehend me?

202
00:21:10,800 --> 00:21:13,159
'Tis a village school
cottagers' daughters

203
00:21:14,760 --> 00:21:17,559
What will you do
with all your fine
accomplishments?

204
00:21:17,760 --> 00:21:20,959
I will save them
till they're wanted.
They will keep.

205
00:21:54,320 --> 00:21:55,319
Jane.

206
00:22:04,320 --> 00:22:06,039
You will be quite
alone here.

207
00:22:06,240 --> 00:22:07,559
I'm not afraid
of solitude.

208
00:22:09,320 --> 00:22:11,239
This is my first home
where I am neither dependent

209
00:22:11,320 --> 00:22:12,679
nor subordinate to anyone.

210
00:22:13,840 --> 00:22:15,679
Thank you, Mr. St. John

211
00:22:19,440 --> 00:22:22,759
It is small and plain
as I told you.

212
00:22:23,760 --> 00:22:25,959
Then it'll suit me
very well.

213
00:22:41,400 --> 00:22:44,119
Safe journey,
Miss Eyre. Godspeed.

214
00:22:44,920 --> 00:22:46,279
Goodbye, Miss Eyre

215
00:22:46,600 --> 00:22:48,119
Safe journey.
Thank you.

216
00:22:48,520 --> 00:22:50,639
Bye, Miss Eyre.

217
00:22:51,280 --> 00:22:52,439
Girls!

218
00:23:02,480 --> 00:23:03,439
Goodbye

219
00:23:11,640 --> 00:23:12,639
Thornfield, Miss.

220
00:23:50,600 --> 00:23:51,999
Wait here, Miss

221
