John is taking your trunk
up to your room.

232
00:24:58,120 --> 00:25:00,399
I've put you at the
back of the house
I hope you don't mind

233
00:25:00,840 --> 00:25:02,919
The rooms at the
front have much
finer furniture,

234
00:25:03,000 --> 00:25:06,239
but they're so gloomy
and solitary, I think.

235
00:25:07,520 --> 00:25:09,079
I'm glad you're come.

236
00:25:10,440 --> 00:25:12,999
To be sure, this is
a grand old house,

237
00:25:13,440 --> 00:25:17,039
but I must confess that
in winter one can fee
a little dreary and alone

238
00:25:17,920 --> 00:25:22,439
Leah's a very nice girl,
and John and Martha
are good people, too,

239
00:25:23,880 --> 00:25:25,919
but they are servants.

240
00:25:26,040 --> 00:25:28,479
One cannot talk to them
on terms of equality

241
00:25:32,400 --> 00:25:34,039
Am I meeting
Miss Fairfax tonight?

242
00:25:34,120 --> 00:25:35,439
Who?

243
00:25:36,080 --> 00:25:37,679
Miss Fairfax
my pupil?

244
00:25:38,400 --> 00:25:40,679
Oh, you mean Miss varens,
Mr. Rochester's ward.

245
00:25:40,800 --> 00:25:42,719
She's to be your pupil

246
00:25:42,800 --> 00:25:44,519
Who's Mr. Rochester?

247
00:25:45,320 --> 00:25:49,639
Why, the owner of Thornfield.
Mr. Edward Fairfax Rochester.

248
00:25:50,760 --> 00:25:52,919
I thought Thornfield Ha
belonged to you.

249
00:25:53,000 --> 00:25:56,359
Bless you, child,
what an idea. Me?

250
00:25:56,800 --> 00:25:58,199
I'm only the housekeeper

251
00:25:58,320 --> 00:25:59,639
Forgive me.

252
00:25:59,720 --> 00:26:02,719
There is a distant
connection between
Mr. Rochester and me

253
00:26:02,800 --> 00:26:06,239
his mother was a Fairfax,
but I'd never presume on it.

254
00:26:06,640 --> 00:26:09,119
Heavens. Me,
owner of Thornfield?

255
00:26:09,800 --> 00:26:12,319
We shall have a cheerful
house this winter

256
